docker/fundamentos-de-docker.richContent:
&lt;h2 id=&quot;conceitos-iniciais&quot;&gt;conceitos iniciais&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#conceitos-iniciais&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;docker √© uma &lt;strong&gt;plataforma de virtualiza√ß√£o&lt;/strong&gt;, que usa conceito de &lt;strong&gt;containers&lt;/strong&gt; para realizar empacotamento e execu√ß√£o de aplica√ß√µes. o container leva o ambiente local para qualquer lugar, de forma leve, r√°pida e isolada do resto do sistema. diferente das m√°quinas virtuais, que t√™m o pr√≥prio sistema operacional complexo e consomem um n√∫mero maior de recursos, os containers compartilham o sistema operacional do host.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;defini√ß√µes&quot;&gt;defini√ß√µes&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#defini√ß√µes&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;../docker/dockerfile&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot; data-slug=&quot;docker/dockerfile&quot;&gt;dockerfile&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;: script que define como criar uma imagem de um container docker, configurando o sistema operacional base, os arquivos e comandos que devem ser executados.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;docker image&lt;/strong&gt;: resultado final do build do &lt;a href=&quot;../docker/dockerfile&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot; data-slug=&quot;docker/dockerfile&quot;&gt;dockerfile&lt;/a&gt;, o run na imagem ir√° resultar no container.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;container&lt;/strong&gt;: uma inst√¢ncia em execu√ß√£o da docker image.&lt;/li&gt;
