java/tipos.richContent:
&lt;p&gt;java √© uma &lt;strong&gt;linguagem fortemente tipada&lt;/strong&gt;, ou seja, precisa da declara√ß√£o de tipos de todas as vari√°veis que s√£o utilizadas no c√≥digo. tipos s√£o como categorias, e definem a natureza dos dados manipulados no c√≥digo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;tipos-primitivos&quot;&gt;tipos primitivos&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#tipos-primitivos&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;representam os valores mais b√°sicos que podem ser usados no c√≥digo. s√£o pr√©-definidos pela linguagem e n√£o podem ser alterados, oferecendo simplicidade e desempenho otimizado. s√£o armazenados diretamente na mem√≥ria,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;int&lt;/code&gt;: armazena n√∫meros inteiros (32 bits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;double&lt;/code&gt;: armazena n√∫meros de ponto flutuante (64 bits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;byte&lt;/code&gt;: armazena n√∫meros inteiros (8 bits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;long&lt;/code&gt;: armazena n√∫meros inteiros (64 bits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;float&lt;/code&gt;: armazena n√∫meros de ponto flutuante (32 bits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;boolean&lt;/code&gt;: armazena valores l√≥gicos, &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt; ou &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt; (1 bit)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;char&lt;/code&gt;: representa um √∫nico caractere unicode (16 bits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;tipos-de-refer√™ncia&quot;&gt;tipos de refer√™ncia&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#tipos-de-refer√™ncia&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;os tipos de refer√™ncia armazenam refer√™ncias (endere√ßos) a objetos na mem√≥ria, em vez de valores em si. fornecem flexibilidade e permitem a cria√ß√£o de estruturas de dados complexas e que se relacionam.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;String&lt;/code&gt;: armazena sequ√™ncias de caracteres, como ‚Äúol√° mundo‚Äù&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;arrays: armazena cole√ß√µes de elementos do mesmo tipo (&lt;code&gt;int[]&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;double[]&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;String[]&lt;/code&gt; etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;classes: classes criadas para representar objetos complexos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

